"use strict";(self.webpackChunkrauljimenez_info=self.webpackChunkrauljimenez_info||[]).push([[1477],{10:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"new-website","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/new-website","editUrl":"https://github.com/hhkaos/hhkaos.github.io/tree/master/blog/2021-08-26-welcome/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2021-08-26-welcome/index.md","title":"Welcome to the new website \ud83c\udd95","description":"Welcome to my new website!, it was time for a change...\ud83d\ude01","date":"2021-08-26T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"August 26, 2021","tags":[{"label":"esri","permalink":"/blog/tags/esri"},{"label":"hello","permalink":"/blog/tags/hello"},{"label":"docusaurus","permalink":"/blog/tags/docusaurus"}],"readingTime":1.34,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Raul Jimenez Ortega","title":"Principal Product Engineer, DevRel @ Esri","url":"https://github.com/hhkaos","imageURL":"https://github.com/hhkaos.png","key":"hhkaos"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"new-website","title":"Welcome to the new website \ud83c\udd95","authors":["hhkaos"],"tags":["esri","hello","docusaurus"]},"nextItem":{"title":"\xa1161 Thanks!, my 31 birthday","permalink":"/blog/cumpleanios-2015"}},"content":"Welcome to my new website!, it was time for a change...\ud83d\ude01\\n\\nSome of you might remember [the old website](http://web.archive.org/web/20160322140938/http://rauljimenez.info/) I built back in 2013:\\n\\n[![Screenshot of rauljimenez.info old website](./rauljimenez.info.png)](http://web.archive.org/web/20160322140938/http://rauljimenez.info/)\\n\\nBack in the days, I decided to build that website to introduce myself, share some thoughts, and give updates about my life to my friends.\\n\\nToday I have decided to replace it for this new website built with [docusaurus.io](https://docusaurus.io/) for several reasons, but mainly because I will be:\\n* **Easier to maintain and update** (no backend and almost everything in [markdown](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markdown)),\\n* Able to **share resources in Spanish and English**.\\n* **Allow you to contribute/repurpose the content I share** (it is [hosted on GitHub](https://github.com/hhkaos/hhkaos.github.io)).\\n\\nSo, the next step is to start migrating the content I could rescue [from my blog](https://blog.rauljimenez.info/) and put it here.\\n\\nI have always thought that it is a pity to create resources and leave them in a drawer, so from now on I plan to start taking many of the resources that I have created over the years and share them in what I have defined as my [\\"\ud83e\udde0 Digital Brain\\"](/docs/digital-brain). \\n\\nI\'m starting by compiling [all the resources I could share](https://github.com/hhkaos/hhkaos.github.io/issues/1), so please, if you are interested in one in particular let me know in the comments.\\n\\nThis tool is not meant to be a social tool where you can subscribe, so if you want to stay up to date on what I share I will be republishing my articles in two channels:\\n* https://medium.com/@hhkaos for Spanish speakers\\n* https://dev.to/hhkaos for English speakers\\n\\nI hope you like it, and any suggestions are more than welcome."},{"id":"cumpleanios-2015","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/cumpleanios-2015","editUrl":"https://github.com/hhkaos/hhkaos.github.io/tree/master/blog/2015-03-12/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2015-03-12/index.md","title":"\xa1161 Thanks!, my 31 birthday","description":"Y\u2026. un a\xf1o m\xe1s no paran de crecer las felicitaciones!! frente a las: 146 de 2014 y 2013, 120 de 2011, 115 de 2010, 89 de 2009 y 48 de 2008.","date":"2015-03-12T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"March 12, 2015","tags":[{"label":"birthday","permalink":"/blog/tags/birthday"}],"readingTime":2.015,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Raul Jimenez Ortega","title":"Principal Product Engineer, DevRel @ Esri","url":"https://github.com/hhkaos","imageURL":"https://github.com/hhkaos.png","key":"hhkaos"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"cumpleanios-2015","authors":["hhkaos"],"tags":["birthday"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Welcome to the new website \ud83c\udd95","permalink":"/blog/new-website"},"nextItem":{"title":"What\'s new since April","permalink":"/blog/lo-sucedido-desde-abril-nov-2014"}},"content":"Y\u2026. un a\xf1o m\xe1s no paran de crecer las felicitaciones!! frente a las: 146 de 2014 y 2013, 120 de 2011, 115 de 2010, 89 de 2009 y 48 de 2008.\\n\\nMuch\xedsimas gracias por acordaros (o tener el detalle de escribirme cuando Facebook/Linkedin/Skype\u2026 os di\xf3 el chivatazo jajaja) a:\\n\\n![Foto de Ra\xfa y su actual mujer](./maria-y-raul.jpeg)\\n\\nEl primer regalito\u2026 by Mar\xeda ^_^\\n\\nPap\xe1, Mam\xe1, Mar\xeda del Mar, Carmen, Brother, Iv\xe1n, Milagros, Verde, Luisette, Mota, Analice, Jose Antonio (Copera!), Dani SEO, Ali Boscan, Sara, Mar\xeda, Patri Zamora (equipoo), Borja Dlb, Oguz, Jorge Ferreiro, Pedro Gonz\xe1lez, Sonia Hern\xe1ndez, Nacho, Javi Rinc\xf3n, Gustavo, Oscar Cum\xed, F\xe1tima, Carlos Iglesias, Ana Mar\xeda Palop, Mari Carmen, Gerardo Casas, Eva Merlo, JJ Merelo, Pepe Moles, Paco Montes, Jos\xe9 de la Chica, Javi Abad\xeda, Alex Hidalgo, Antonio Remirez, Irene, Loli, Milagros, Pepe y Jose (familia pol\xedtica! :D), Estrellas, Patri Romero, Aida M, Bel\xe9n Carvajal, Cristina Gonz\xe1lez, Fernando Benito, Tomas, Sergio Lillo, Silvia Bootello, Belen, M\xf3nica, Almudena, Jorge Margenta, Mat\xedas, Jordi P\xe9rez, Kini, Tita Angelines, prima Isabel Pilar, \xc1lvaro Mora, Ana Paniagua, Pelos, Pablo Capilla, Guaning, Luisa, Alejando (Mr Simar), Celia Maracena, \xc1lvaro Maracena, Nico (Maracena), Gerardo (Maracena), Jose (cabeza), Roc\xedo (Fever), Isaac, Marta (prima), Jos\xe9 Manuel Cartes, Josep, Pili D\xedaz, Zam, Gloria, Alex Vega, V\xedctor, Antonio (Tony Ryan), Jason, Ana MC, Nu\xf1o, Juancho, David Cuenca, Pablo Hinojosa, Mar\xeda Platero, Guille, Chaparro, Antonio Rabago, Karla, Javier Rivero, Oliver Calvo, Luis A. Nerja, Tita In\xe9s, David Arroyo, Nieves, Paula, Natath, Miguel Calero, Jessica Plegue, Elaine. Francesc y Tita Espe, primo Oliver, Guillermo Sanz, Tita Pili y Tito Paco, Yirli, Diego Ba\xf1ales, prima Pilar, Fede , Francesc, Jorge Barrachina, Jes\xfas Garc\xeda Villar, Juasmilla, Fernando MTC, Milu, abuela, AngelID, Jon Garrido, Uri, Fran canario, Mari Carmen L\xf3pez, Rubert Pacheco, Mar\xeda Gonz\xe1lez Jaime, Cristina Granados, Jos\xe9 Manuel Robles, Andr\xe9s Bayona, Yisus, Max, Jos\xe9 M\xaa Berlanga, Juan Antonio Franco Rojas, Eugenio Morarescu, Antonio Fdez Ares ,Gonzalo Fdez, Virginia, Pascual, Pozu, Santiago Aguilera, Mercedes, Sergio Jim\xe9nez, Chilli, Rufa, Dani Molina, Miguel Fdez Calero, Manu (Quea), Yusep, Fran Servia, David Gal\xe1n, Noelia Rodr\xedguez, Marina Azagra, Priscila, Fernando Rodr\xedguez Le\xf3n, Miguel \xc1ngel Lozano y Dugo!!\\n\\nY\u2026. perdonad una vez m\xe1s si me he dejado a algun@! que es mu complicao llevar la lista con tantos canales: felicitaciones en persona, por facebook (muro+mensajes), llamadas, whastapp, hangouts, sms\u2019s, linkedin, mails, etc.\\n\\nGracias una vez m\xe1s y \u2026 \xa1hasta el a\xf1o que viene! (como sol\xedamos decir de peque\xf1os\u2026 si Johnnie Walker quiere! ;-P)"},{"id":"lo-sucedido-desde-abril-nov-2014","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/lo-sucedido-desde-abril-nov-2014","editUrl":"https://github.com/hhkaos/hhkaos.github.io/tree/master/blog/2014-11-02/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2014-11-02/index.md","title":"What\'s new since April","description":"Google Glass y Android Wear","date":"2014-11-02T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"November 2, 2014","tags":[{"label":"experiences","permalink":"/blog/tags/experiences"}],"readingTime":1.99,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Raul Jimenez Ortega","title":"Principal Product Engineer, DevRel @ Esri","url":"https://github.com/hhkaos","imageURL":"https://github.com/hhkaos.png","key":"hhkaos"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"lo-sucedido-desde-abril-nov-2014","authors":["hhkaos"],"tags":["experiences"]},"prevItem":{"title":"\xa1161 Thanks!, my 31 birthday","permalink":"/blog/cumpleanios-2015"},"nextItem":{"title":"How Google Glass works","permalink":"/blog/como-funcionan-las-google-glass"}},"content":"### Google Glass y Android Wear\\n\\nAunque ya os cont\xe9 que hab\xeda conseguido unas Google Glass y\xa0[c\xf3mo funcionaban](/blog/como-funcionan-las-google-glass), desde Septiembre tambi\xe9n tengo un\xa0[G Watch](https://play.google.com/store/devices/details/LG_G_Watch_Black_Titan?id=lg_g_watch_black&hl=en)\xa0con Android Wear. Adem\xe1s me he animado a desarrollar una aplicaci\xf3n de alertas geolocalizadas b\xe1sica que funciona tanto\xa0[en el reloj](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lImhDJYrnt4&list=PLwq5dz_FjCx7Q8qLN45nJqNXz7hBdNgeN)\xa0como\xa0[en las gafas](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TVvgNtIxdNo&list=PLwq5dz_FjCx7Q8qLN45nJqNXz7hBdNgeN&index=3).\\n\\n[![](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740im_/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Screenshot-2014-07-13-13.51.23-250x175.png)](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2014/07/13/como-funcionan-las-google-glass/)\\n\\n### Ganamos el 1er hackathon BEEVA\\n\\nEl 25 de Septiembre particip\xe9 en un Hackathon de BEEVA (de BBVA) donde ganamos el primer premio con el desarrollo de un prototipo de aplicaci\xf3n de promociones geolocalizadas en smartwatches con\xa0[Android Wear](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/https://developer.android.com/wear/index.html)\xa0y\xa0[ArcGIS Online](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://developers.arcgis.com/en/).\\n\\n[![2014-09-30_09h55_32](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740im_/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/2014-09-30_09h55_32.png)](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/2014-09-30_09h55_32.png)\\n\\n### Iniciador Madrid\\n\\nEl d\xeda 26 de Septiembre estuve en el Global Meeting de Iniciador, un evento que organiz\xf3 la\xa0[Fundaci\xf3n Iniciador](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://iniciador.com/)\xa0para organizadores y ex-organizadores con el objetivo de tratar varios temas que afectan a la organizaci\xf3n.\\n\\nAll\xed pude reencontrarme con muchos viejos amigos y conoc\xed a otros nuevos, pero lo mejor es que despu\xe9s de aquel evento he decidido volver a colaborar en Iniciador tanto a nivel nacional como a nivel local, por lo que a partir de este mes estar\xe9 ya estar\xe9 ayudando en la organizaci\xf3n de\xa0[Iniciador Madrid](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://iniciador.com/madrid/).\\n\\n[![GMIniciador](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740im_/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/GMIniciador.jpg)](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/GMIniciador.jpg)\\n\\nFoto en el Global Meeting\\n\\n### Afterwork\\n\\nEl 6 de Octubre estuve en\xa0[Capital Radio\xa0en el programa Afterwork](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://www.capitalradio.es/programas/after-work/)\xa0en una entrevista a\xa0[Enrique O\u2019Connor](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://es.linkedin.com/in/enriqueoconnor)\xa0fundador de\xa0[Spotlinker](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://www.spotlinker.com/).\\n\\n![](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740im_/https://media.licdn.com/mpr/mpr/shrink_200_200/p/1/000/0f3/03c/2059c5f.jpg)\\n\\nEnrique O\u2019Connor\\n\\nAudio Player\\n\\n00:00\\n\\nUse Left/Right Arrow keys to advance one second, Up/Down arrows to advance ten seconds.\\n\\n00:00\\n\\nUse Up/Down Arrow keys to increase or decrease volume.\\n\\n### Conferencia Esri Espa\xf1a\\n\\nLos d\xedas 22 y 23 de Octubre celebramos la\xa0[conferencia anual de Esri Espa\xf1a](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://evento.esri.es/es/ce14/?utm_source=home-esri-es), un macro evento donde ense\xf1amos toda la potencia de la plataforma\xa0[ArcGIS](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://developers.arcgis.com/en/)\xa0a profesionales de todo tipo. Os dejo un v\xeddeo donde ense\xf1\xe9 una mini aplicaci\xf3n que desarroll\xe9 para mi reloj con\xa0[Android Wear](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/https://developer.android.com/wear/index.html)\xa0^_^.\\n\\nTodos los v\xeddeos de la conferencia los pod\xe9is encontrar en la cuenta de\xa0[Esri Espa\xf1a en Youtube](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLoptan2utx17yQLSiUPiJeqtMD_LPb9H0).\\n\\n[![Conferencia Esri Espana](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740im_/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Conferencia-Esri-Espana.jpg)](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/Conferencia-Esri-Espana.jpg)\\n\\nDurante mi ponencia en la sesi\xf3n plenaria\\n\\n### Tour en universidades\\n\\nDurante el mes de Octubre tambi\xe9n he estado haciendo un\xa0[Tour por las universidades](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://desarrolladores.esri.es/geo-developer-communities/)\xa0de Sevilla, Castell\xf3n, Complutense de Madrid y Pompeu Fabra en (Barcelona) para explicarles las oportunidades profesionales que tienen si se especializan en el desarrollo de aplicaciones usando tecnolog\xedas como las que ofrecemos en Esri ([ArcGIS](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://developers.arcgis.com/en/)).\\n\\n![GeoDevUJI](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740im_/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/GeoDevUJI.jpg)\\n\\nCharla en la Universitat Jaume I en Castell\xf3n\\n\\n### Google Developer Festival\\n\\nEl viernes 31 de Octubre estuve en la Facultad de Granada en el\xa0[Google Developer Festival](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://devfest.gdggranada.com/)\xa0hablando de dispositivos wearables con las Google Glass, Android Wear y\xa0[ArcGIS Online](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/https://developers.arcgis.com/en/).\\n\\n[![B1RQZUGCUAAXImr](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740im_/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/B1RQZUGCUAAXImr.jpg \\"Mi ponencia en el Devfest\\")](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419165740/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/B1RQZUGCUAAXImr.jpg)"},{"id":"como-funcionan-las-google-glass","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/como-funcionan-las-google-glass","editUrl":"https://github.com/hhkaos/hhkaos.github.io/tree/master/blog/2014-07-13/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2014-07-13/index.md","title":"How Google Glass works","description":"Hace ya bastante tiempo que quer\xeda experimentar c\xf3mo funcionan las\xa0Google Glass, y despu\xe9s de una larga espera ya lo he podido vivir en mis propias carnes (y con calma). As\xed que para aquellos que ten\xedais las mismas preguntas que yo, he decidido grabar estos v\xeddeos en los que trato de explicar c\xf3mo funcionan.","date":"2014-07-13T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"July 13, 2014","tags":[{"label":"google-glass","permalink":"/blog/tags/google-glass"}],"readingTime":0.595,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Raul Jimenez Ortega","title":"Principal Product Engineer, DevRel @ Esri","url":"https://github.com/hhkaos","imageURL":"https://github.com/hhkaos.png","key":"hhkaos"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"como-funcionan-las-google-glass","authors":["hhkaos"],"tags":["google-glass"]},"prevItem":{"title":"What\'s new since April","permalink":"/blog/lo-sucedido-desde-abril-nov-2014"},"nextItem":{"title":"Having a poor memory it\'s not so bad","permalink":"/blog/mala-memoria"}},"content":"Hace ya bastante tiempo que quer\xeda experimentar c\xf3mo funcionan las\xa0[Google Glass](http://www.google.es/glass/start/), y despu\xe9s de una larga espera ya lo he podido vivir en mis propias carnes (y con calma). As\xed que para aquellos que ten\xedais las mismas preguntas que yo, he decidido grabar estos v\xeddeos en los que trato de explicar c\xf3mo funcionan.\\n\\n\x3c!-- En este primer v\xeddeo explico un poco\xa0**el funcionamiento de la interfaz**: --\x3e\\n\\n\\nEn este v\xeddeo hago una\xa0**mini demo**\xa0(hasta donde las gafas me dejaron xD):\\n\\n<iframe width=\\"560\\" height=\\"315\\" src=\\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/TVvgNtIxdNo\\" title=\\"YouTube video player\\" frameborder=\\"0\\" allow=\\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\\n\\nMe encantar\xeda que me dijeseis si se entiende bien, que me pregunt\xe9is las dudas que os queden, si quer\xe9is ver algo concreto, etc.\\n\\n\xa1Un abrazo!"},{"id":"mala-memoria","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/mala-memoria","editUrl":"https://github.com/hhkaos/hhkaos.github.io/tree/master/blog/2014-04-20/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2014-04-20/index.md","title":"Having a poor memory it\'s not so bad","description":"Hoy quer\xeda compartir otra reflexi\xf3n que he tenido, esta vez es que: \u201ctodo tiene un lado positivo, incluso tener mala memoria\u201c, aunque quiz\xe1s Leonard Shelby (de\xa0Memento)) no pensar\xeda lo mismo xD.","date":"2014-04-20T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"April 20, 2014","tags":[{"label":"memory","permalink":"/blog/tags/memory"},{"label":"thoughts","permalink":"/blog/tags/thoughts"}],"readingTime":1.565,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Raul Jimenez Ortega","title":"Principal Product Engineer, DevRel @ Esri","url":"https://github.com/hhkaos","imageURL":"https://github.com/hhkaos.png","key":"hhkaos"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"mala-memoria","authors":["hhkaos"],"tags":["memory","thoughts"]},"prevItem":{"title":"How Google Glass works","permalink":"/blog/como-funcionan-las-google-glass"},"nextItem":{"title":"My new job at Esri","permalink":"/blog/mi-nuevo-trabajo-en-esri"}},"content":"Hoy quer\xeda compartir otra reflexi\xf3n que he tenido, esta vez es que: \u201c**todo tiene un lado positivo, incluso tener mala memoria**\u201c, aunque quiz\xe1s Leonard Shelby (de\xa0[Memento](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419185718/http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Memento_(film))) no pensar\xeda lo mismo xD.\\n\\n![](./memento.png)\\n\\nLos que me conoc\xe9is sab\xe9is que soy una persona bastante activa, siempre estoy con nuevas ideas, proyectos, etc. y sab\xe9is que siempre suelo decir que tengo mala memoria (lo cual es cierto).\xa0A veces pienso que es porque no ejercito mucho la memoria, aunque a veces pienso que se debe a mi \u201chiperactividad\u201d.\\n\\nVete t\xfa a saber por qu\xe9\u2026. la cosa es que a veces \u201cme da rabia\u201d pensar que \u201csoy as\xed\u201d, pero esta vez me he pasado a pensar y he dicho\u2026 bueno\u2026 tener mala memoria no siempre es malo. \xbfPor qu\xe9?, en mi opini\xf3n porque:\\n\\n1.  **Me obliga a ser m\xe1s estructurado**, por ejemplo:\\n    -   Cuando se trata de trabajo intento de documentar todos los procedimientos\\n    -   Procedimientos o trabajo que luego comparto; por ejemplo en art\xedculos de este blog como:\xa0[Pacto de socios](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419185718/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2014/04/06/pacto-de-socios/),\xa0[Plantilla para crear un plan de anal\xedtica](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419185718/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2014/01/06/plantilla-para-crear-un-plan-de-analitica/), etc.\\n    -   Tiendo a usar bastantes herramientas de gesti\xf3n de tareas que luego reutilizo en mi trabajo.\\n2.  Adem\xe1s\xa0**me obligo a escribir m\xe1s**\xa0sobre lo que he hecho para no olvidarlo\\n    1.  Sin ir m\xe1s lejos, mis posts de\xa0[resumen de vida](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419185718/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/category/sobre-mi/)\xa0que adem\xe1s me sirven para mantener a mis amig@s al d\xeda de c\xf3mo estoy.\\n    2.  Y a compartir\xa0[art\xedculos como este](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419185718/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2013/12/08/el-trabajo-perfecto/), que son razonamientos que quiero interiorizar (y escribirlo ayuda).\\n3.  Y por \xfaltimo tambi\xe9n\xa0**ayuda a que se te olviden antes los problemas o a quitarles importancia**\xa0a muchos de ellos.\\n\\nEn definitiva, si alguien alguna vez os critica por tener mala memoria, a lo mejor ya pod\xe9is contra argumentar que \u2026 tener mala memoria tambi\xe9n tiene sus ventajas, \xbfqu\xe9 me dec\xeds?.\\n\\nPor cierto, este razonamiento tambi\xe9n se aplica a \u201c**tener atenci\xf3n dispersa**\u201c, \xbfalguien se atreve a justificar lo bueno que tiene esto? ^_^"},{"id":"mi-nuevo-trabajo-en-esri","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/mi-nuevo-trabajo-en-esri","editUrl":"https://github.com/hhkaos/hhkaos.github.io/tree/master/blog/2014-04-17/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2014-04-17/index.md","title":"My new job at Esri","description":"Como ya adelant\xe9 en mi\xa0ante-pen\xfaltimo art\xedculo\xa0me he unido al equipo de Esri Espa\xf1a como\xa0Developer Program Manager\u2026 \xbfy eso en qu\xe9 consiste? pues muy sencillo: en ayudar e inspirar a los desarrolladores para que creen aplicaciones que resuelvan problemas relacionados con la localizaci\xf3n (ya sea del usuario o de cualquier otra cosa).","date":"2014-04-17T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"April 17, 2014","tags":[{"label":"work","permalink":"/blog/tags/work"}],"readingTime":1.585,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Raul Jimenez Ortega","title":"Principal Product Engineer, DevRel @ Esri","url":"https://github.com/hhkaos","imageURL":"https://github.com/hhkaos.png","key":"hhkaos"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"mi-nuevo-trabajo-en-esri","authors":["hhkaos"],"tags":["work"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Having a poor memory it\'s not so bad","permalink":"/blog/mala-memoria"},"nextItem":{"title":"Investing in online training","permalink":"/blog/invertir-en-formacion-online"}},"content":"Como ya adelant\xe9 en mi\xa0[ante-pen\xfaltimo art\xedculo](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2014/03/28/resumen-de-los-sucedido-desde-agosto/ \\"Resumen de lo sucedido desde Agosto\\")\xa0me he unido al equipo de Esri Espa\xf1a como\xa0**Developer Program Manager**\u2026 \xbfy eso en qu\xe9 consiste? pues muy sencillo: en ayudar e inspirar a los desarrolladores para que creen aplicaciones que resuelvan problemas relacionados con la localizaci\xf3n (ya sea del usuario o de cualquier otra cosa).\\n\\n[![Foto del Developer summit, desarrolladores jugando a ping pong](./pingpong-esri.jpeg)](https://www.flickr.com/photos/esri/sets/)\\n\\nEsri Developers Summit en EEUU\\n\\nPara los que no os suena la empresa os comento que\xa0[Esri](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/http://www.esri.com/)\xa0es una empresa que nace en Estados Unidos hace m\xe1s de 40 a\xf1os (actualmente con m\xe1s de 3000 trabajadores\xa0[en todo el mundo](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/http://www.esri.com/about-esri/offices)) y que en mi opini\xf3n ha creado el mejor software del sector de los Sistemas de Informaci\xf3n Geogr\xe1fica (SIG):\xa0[ArcGIS](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/http://arcgis.com/).\\n\\n[![esri](./esri-logo.png)](http://www.esri.com/)\\n\\n\xbfY eso para qu\xe9 se usa?, pues os pongo varios ejemplos para que situ\xe9is, por ejemplo para:\\n\\n-   Identificar cuales son las\xa0[mejores zona para vivir dentro de una ciudad](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/http://uji.maps.arcgis.com/apps/Filter/index.html?appid=96848387cd1a4ffeaf0bbc1a98699640)\xa0(en base a unos criterios)\\n-   Resolver problemas como:\xa0[\xbfcu\xe1l es la mejor localizaci\xf3n para montar mi pr\xf3ximo negocio?](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/http://www.forbes.com/sites/barbarathau/2014/04/24/how-big-data-helps-retailers-like-starbucks-pick-store-locations-an-unsung-key-to-retail-success/)\\n-   Crear\xa0[aplicaciones m\xf3vil que sean conscientes de su localizaci\xf3n](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/http://www.fastcolabs.com/3028819/the-big-question-in-retail-now-is-what-are-you-doing-with-geotriggers)\xa0e incorporen comportamientos asociados a la misma.\\n-   [Montar escenarios 3D din\xe1micos e interactivos](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/http://www.arcgis.com/apps/CEWebViewer/viewer.html?3dWebScene=9c0e319bfaff4d33a0fe2da97c2c3fd7)\xa0(al estilo Second Life)\\n-   Representar y comunicar grandes cantidades de informaci\xf3n de manera m\xe1s comprensible ([mapa de inglaterra](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/http://illustreets.co.uk/explore-england)) o atractiva ([mapa con lugares incre\xedbles](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/http://www.arcgis.com/apps/MapTour/?appid=35926d0e1c7741b59948ca45f4f33b3a)).\\n-   [Realizar simulaciones](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/http://mappingpoint.blogspot.com.es/2014/01/terremotos-en-la-isla-del-hierro.html), analizar datos geolocalizados ([por ejemplo compras](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/http://grupoweb.upf.es:8080/quartz/))\xa0y predecir situaciones futuras ([colas en tiendas, etc](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/https://www.centrodeinnovacionbbva.com/en/pages/29293-winners)).\\n-   [Otros ejemplos](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/http://www.geoases.com/inspiracion/)\\n\\nO sea que se puede usar tanto para resolver problemas, optimizar procesos, comunicar mejor, etc. y por tanto las aplicaciones que se les puede dar son millones y pueden ser \xfatiles tanto para personas a pie de calle como para empresas y gobiernos.\\n\\nSi eres programador y te interesa aprender m\xe1s sobre este mundillo te invito a que te\xa0**[unas al Meetup de Geo Developers](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438/http://www.meetup.com/Geo-Developers/)**\xa0que he creado con el fin de organizar charlas, talleres, etc. y que nos ayudemos mutuamente compartiendo conocimientos.\\n\\n\xa1Hasta pronto!\xa0![:D](https://web.archive.org/web/20150419172438im_/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif)"},{"id":"invertir-en-formacion-online","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/invertir-en-formacion-online","editUrl":"https://github.com/hhkaos/hhkaos.github.io/tree/master/blog/2014-01-04/index.md","source":"@site/blog/2014-01-04/index.md","title":"Investing in online training","description":"A\xa0muchos a\xfan les cuesta dar el paso de decidirse a pagar una cuota para suscribirse a un buen servicio de formaci\xf3n online; y yo quer\xeda romper hoy una lanza por ella porque creo que es m\xe1s rentable frente a otras alternativas de formaci\xf3n regladas. En mi caso decid\xed hacer una apuesta en Junio del a\xf1o pasado por\xa0CodeSchool, para mi\xa0la mejor plataforma\xa0que existe para mantenerse actualizado y\xa0mejorar las habilidades en cuanto a programaci\xf3n.","date":"2014-01-04T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"January 4, 2014","tags":[{"label":"education","permalink":"/blog/tags/education"}],"readingTime":1.845,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Raul Jimenez Ortega","title":"Principal Product Engineer, DevRel @ Esri","url":"https://github.com/hhkaos","imageURL":"https://github.com/hhkaos.png","key":"hhkaos"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"invertir-en-formacion-online","authors":["hhkaos"],"tags":["education"]},"prevItem":{"title":"My new job at Esri","permalink":"/blog/mi-nuevo-trabajo-en-esri"}},"content":"A\xa0muchos a\xfan les cuesta dar el paso de decidirse a pagar una cuota para suscribirse a un buen servicio de formaci\xf3n online; y yo quer\xeda romper hoy una lanza por ella porque creo que es m\xe1s rentable frente a otras alternativas de formaci\xf3n regladas. En mi caso decid\xed hacer una apuesta en Junio del a\xf1o pasado por\xa0[CodeSchool](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/http://www.codeschool.com/), para mi\xa0**la mejor plataforma**\xa0que existe para mantenerse actualizado y\xa0**mejorar las habilidades en cuanto a programaci\xf3n**.\\n\\nA mi personalmente en cuanto a plataformas de educaci\xf3n, me gustan m\xe1s aquellas que me obligan a entregar ejercicios para obtener la certificaci\xf3n ya que suponen poner en pr\xe1ctica lo aprendido y por tanto creo que aportan cierta validez. Os dejo otro par de plataformas con MOOCs que siguen esta l\xednea donde podr\xe9is encontrar cursos gratuitos (con certificaciones de pago):\xa0[Coursera](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/http://coursera.org/),\xa0[Miriadax](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/http://miriadax.net/),\xa0[CodeAcademy](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/http://www.codecademy.com/)\xa0y\xa0[EDX](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/https://www.edx.org/)\xa0(_gracias Pino por esta \xfaltima!_).\\n\\nBueno, pues en mi caso pago una cuota de\xa0**25 d\xf3lares al mes**\xa0en Codeschool, lo que en estos meses (con descuentos incluidos) han sido unos 125\u20ac y aunque pueda parecer una cantidad considerable, creo que si analizamos lo que he adquirido a cambio le da otra perspectiva diferente.\\n\\nPor ejemplo, yo en este tiempo\xa0[he hecho 9](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/https://www.codeschool.com/users/227734)\xa0de los 36 cursos que tienen disponibles:\\n\\n\u2013\xa0[Javascript Road Trip Part 1](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/https://www.codeschool.com/courses/javascript-road-trip-part-1)\xa0**(Gratuito)**  \\n\u2013\xa0[Javascript Road Trip Part 2](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/https://www.codeschool.com/courses/javascript-road-trip-part-2)  \\n\u2013\xa0[Javascript Road Trip Part 3  \\n](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/https://www.codeschool.com/courses/javascript-road-trip-part-3)-\xa0[Coffeescript](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/https://www.codeschool.com/courses/coffeescript)  \\n\u2013\xa0[Real-Time-Web with Node.js](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/https://www.codeschool.com/courses/real-time-web-with-nodejs)  \\n\u2013\xa0[Discover DevTools](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/https://www.codeschool.com/courses/discover-devtools)\xa0**(Gratuito)**  \\n\u2013\xa0[Fundamentals of Design](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/https://www.codeschool.com/courses/fundamentals-of-design)  \\n\u2013\xa0[Try Git](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/https://www.codeschool.com/courses/try-git)\xa0**(Gratuito)**  \\n\u2013\xa0[Try Ruby](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/https://www.codeschool.com/courses/try-ruby)\\n\\nHaciendo las cuentas cada curso de pago me ha salido por unos 20\u20ac y les he invertido \u2026 dir\xeda que entre 4 y 8 horas a cada uno. Si hacemos las cuentas creo que sale a un precio bastante razonable ya que los cursos son de una tremenda calidad e incluyen un mont\xf3n de ejercicios pr\xe1cticos que creo\xa0**me est\xe1n haciendo un mejor profesional**.\\n\\n\xbfQu\xe9 opin\xe1is vosotros al respecto?, en\xa0**comparaci\xf3n con otras posibilidades de formaci\xf3n**: talleres, workshops de formaci\xf3n, masters, etc.\xa0**\xbfno os parece un buen precio?**.\\n\\n### Art\xedculos relacionados\\n\\n-   [![Gamificaci\xf3n, \xbfpor qu\xe9 gamificar?](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822im_/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2013/04/gamification_wordle1-150x150.jpg)](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2013/04/14/gamificacion-por-que-gamificar/)[Gamificaci\xf3n, \xbfpor qu\xe9 gamificar?](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2013/04/14/gamificacion-por-que-gamificar/)\\n-   [![Practicando lo aprendido sobre usabilidad](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822im_/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/08/Inicio-150x150.png)](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2010/08/15/practicando-lo-aprendido-sobre-usabilidad/)[Practicando lo aprendido sobre usabilidad](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2010/08/15/practicando-lo-aprendido-sobre-usabilidad/)\\n-   [![Material de nuestro curso sobre las TIC (muy b\xe1sico)](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822im_/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/internet-products-150x150.jpg)](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2010/03/19/material-de-nuestro-curso-sobre-las-tic-muy-basico/)[Material de nuestro curso sobre las TIC (muy b\xe1sico)](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2010/03/19/material-de-nuestro-curso-sobre-las-tic-muy-basico/)\\n-   [![Curso gratuito de XHTML+CSS](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822im_/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2009/04/plan-actividades-150x150.jpg)](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2009/04/16/curso-gratuito-de-xhtmlcss/)[Curso gratuito de XHTML+CSS](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2009/04/16/curso-gratuito-de-xhtmlcss/)\\n-   [![Introducci\xf3n a Subversion \u2013 1er Hackaton](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822im_/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/5613614859_cd5ddd1ba9-150x150.jpg)](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2010/03/05/introduccion-a-subversion-1er-hackaton/)[Introducci\xf3n a Subversion \u2013 1er Hackaton](https://web.archive.org/web/20160531110822/http://www.rauljimenez.info/blog/2010/03/05/introduccion-a-subversion-1er-hackaton/)"}]}')}}]);